<p>half the fighting we have been through, our boys have done wonderful good work at Pozieres &amp; it will be more widely known one of these days after the war though even now all the English papers have nothing but praise for the Australians &amp; their work. I went along afterwards to the 26th 24th 23rd but could find no more of our boys, so I expect they are at Camiers or Bologne.</p>
<p>21st.    All tents are struck this morning &amp; everything packed up neatly.   There is a big medical examination in the camp today.</p>
